--ROADMAP for FEBRUARY--

Week 1: Encodings & Classic Ciphers

Days 1-2: Complete picoCTF basic encoding challenges ("Mod 26", "bases", and "The Numbers").

Days 3-4: Tackle CryptoHack "ASCII" and complete OverTheWire Krypton Levels 0-1 to get comfortable with the command line.

Days 5-7: Practice by finding and solving 5-10 more easy historical ciphers (Caesar, Substitution) on picoCTF.


Week 2: Math & Modern Foundations

Days 1-2: Complete CryptoHack "Greatest Common Divisor (GCD)" and "Modular Arithmetic 1".

Days 3-4: Dive into RSA by solving picoCTF "Mind your Ps and Qs" (focus on understanding prime factoring).

Days 5-6: Complete picoCTF "Easy1" and CryptoHack "XOR Starter" to master bitwise operations.


Week 3: Automation & Applied Cryptanalysis

Days 1-2: Complete CryptoPals Set 1, Challenges 1 & 2 (Scripting Hex to Base64 and Fixed XOR in Python).

Days 3-4: Complete CryptoPals Set 1, Challenge 3 (Automating Single-byte XOR with frequency analysis scoring).

Days 5-6: Complete picoCTF "New Caesar" and CryptoHack "Passwords as Keys" (focusing on brute-forcing weak keys).



Week 4: Real-World Application & Assessment Week

Days 1-2: Review all scripts written so far. Re-solve the hardest challenge from Week 3 without looking at your previous code.

Days 3-4: Attempt 2 medium-difficulty challenges on CryptoHack involving either AES or RSA.


